
[1]christ

   CHRIST, n. THE ANOINTED; an appellation given to the Savior of the
   World, and synonymous with the Hebrew Messiah. It was a custom of
   antiquity to consecrate persons to the sacerdotal and regal offices by
   anointing them with oil.
